## Commands

```bash
pip install -e ".[dev]"   # Install with dev deps
pytest tests/ -v          # Run all tests
pytest tests/test_x.py -v # Run single test file
ruff check .              # Lint
ruff format .             # Format
```

## Architecture

- `src/{{PACKAGE}}/` — Package source
- `tests/` — Tests (mirror src/ structure)
- `pyproject.toml` — Project config and dependencies

## Code Style

- Type hints on all public functions
- f-strings over .format() or %
- Pathlib over os.path
- Max 200 lines per file, max 50 lines per function

## Testing

- Run single test files during development: `pytest tests/test_x.py::test_name -v`
- Use fixtures over setUp/tearDown
- No mocks unless testing external services
- Default: `pytest --timeout=120 -x -q` (stop on first failure)

## Security

- Never commit `.env`, API keys, or credentials
- Reference secrets by env var name only
- Use `os.environ.get("VAR_NAME", "")` with fallback defaults

## AI Workflow

- Every feature: **Spec → Plan → Code → Test → Refactor** — never skip spec/plan
- One module at a time (narrow slices) — no big-bang system generation
- Never accept first output — run a critique pass before committing
- Always run code locally before claiming done — paste exact errors, not descriptions
- `/clear` after ~20 file reads or major topic shifts

